{"tid":2368291,"cid":5,"subCid":11,"title":"特朗普獲摩洛哥頒發最高荣誉獎，表揚他對中東和平的貢獻","createTime":"2021-01-16T05:20:47.000Z","updateTime":"2021-01-17T00:44:54.000Z","uid":256837,"like":989,"dislike":18,"uniUserReply":98,"replies":[{"pid":"7fa7b585fb49c29e48698cbe2244c807b2d1bd25","tid":2368291,"uid":256837,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:20:47.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2021/01/332100/us-president-donald-trump-receives-highest-award-from-morocco/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.moroccoworldnews.com%2F2021%2F01%2F332100%2Fus-president-donald-trump-receives-highest-award-from-morocco%2F&d=urW02bDNsyUCiNuSwPhOyODT5CHOggjCyLUuLmpgHOg%3D&h=e3650f0a\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.moroccoworldnews.com/2021/01/332100/us-president-donald-trump-receives-highest-award-from-morocco/</a><br />\n<br />\nRabat &ndash; US President Donald Trump reportedly received Morocco&rsquo;s highest award today for peace efforts enabling Rabat and Tel Aviv to restore relations.<br />\n<br />\nReuters quoted a senior White House official, saying that Morocco&rsquo;s Ambassador to the US  Princess Lalla Joumala presented Trump with the award, called the Order of Muhammad, in a private ceremony. <br />\n<br />\nThe award was a gift from Morocco&rsquo;s King Mohammed VI.<br />\n<br />\nMorocco also gave two other awards to Trump&rsquo;s Senior Adviser Jared Kushner and Middle East Envoy Avi Berkowitz.<br />\n<br />\nThe awards came to recognize senior officials&rsquo; efforts in restoring relations between Morocco and Israel.<br />\n<br />\nMorocco announced its decision to establish diplomatic ties with Israel on December 10. The decision included vows from Tel Aviv and Rabat to see their cooperation advance at all levels, including trade.<br />\n<br />\nThe two countries also plan to reopen their liaison offices, and will launch direct fights in the two or three coming months.<br />\n<br />\nMorocco, Israel, and the US also signed a Joint Declaration on December 22, officializing the diplomatic relations between Rabat and Tel Aviv.<br />\n<br />\nHead of Government Saad Eddine El Othmani signed the declaration along with Israel&rsquo;s National Security Adviser Meir Ben Shabbat and Jared Kushner.<br />\n<br />\nThe US received applause from Israel for its peace efforts, which enabled Tel Aviv to restore relations with several countries, including Bahrain, the UAE, Sudan, along with Morocco.<br />\n<br />\nTrump vowed that more countries will join the four countries in the future, including Saudi Arabia.<br />\n<br />\nMorocco and the US share strong diplomatic relations, with both countries regularly vowing to strengthen cooperation further.<br />\n<br />\nThe bonds experienced a boost after the US recognized Morocco&rsquo;s sovereignty over Western Sahara on December 10."},{"pid":"13df42850ca2c338e91aa5402df624f3a7bd7555","tid":2368291,"uid":2054,"like":104,"dislike":1,"score":103,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:21:49.000Z","msg":"Big Tech又要郁手"},{"pid":"5788421356f2878b73971b20e7649ee15bcdb316","tid":2368291,"uid":228868,"like":78,"dislike":5,"score":73,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:23:43.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/pig/angry.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />好嬲<br />\n利：愛登力"},{"pid":"c231d5a0dad6c3a93c6eccb5d966f0c633344d8b","tid":2368291,"uid":9193,"like":103,"dislike":2,"score":101,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:25:10.000Z","msg":"誉<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"ad2c09381a29d3ef49fdd0734fe3357f97625117","tid":2368291,"uid":55913,"like":33,"dislike":1,"score":32,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:30:09.000Z","msg":"真&middot;美國總統"},{"pid":"0ae80b433dbec3b139d01b4cd96fc99a106a775f","tid":2368291,"uid":175479,"like":21,"dislike":0,"score":21,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2021-01-16T05:30:40.000Z","msg":"Block得，快啲通知左膠啦"},{"pid":"b919306261858145b93f8e07f7fcdf8892f7faf2","tid":2368291,"uid":2